**Which version of Sharding-Sphere did you use?**
answer：<sharding-sphere.version>3.0.0</sharding-sphere.version>

**Which project did you use? Sharding-JDBC or Sharding-Proxy?**
 Sharding-JDBC 

**Expected behavior**
Insert 4 million pieces of data into the mysql database (mysql version 5.2.65), the data is completely inserted correctly. and Execute the query.

**Actual behavior**
		UserInfoExample example = new UserInfoExample();
		example.createCriteria().andPasswordEqualTo("password 0");
		example.setOrderByClause("create_time");
		List<UserInfo> users = userInfoMapper.selectByExample(example);
		
	The occurred above user_id duplicate problem , I confirmed that the database data is no problem. Only the results of the query appeared。
	
	Then I changed the test code：
		UserInfoExample example = new UserInfoExample();
		example.createCriteria().andUserIdBetween(279023793651843071L, 279023793651843074L);
		example.setOrderByClause("create_time");
		List<UserInfo> users = userInfoMapper.selectByExample(example);
		
	The problem is still，And the result that user_id=279023793651843071L is not in the query range appears. But only part of the data has this problem,
	
	
		
**Reason analyze (If you can)**
I really don't understand.  Because not all of these problems occur, the same execution statement,  different query conditions have no problems.

	Example I test query like this , is no problem ：
		UserInfoExample example = new UserInfoExample();
		example.createCriteria().andPasswordEqualTo("password 555500");
		example.setOrderByClause("create_time");
		List<UserInfo> users = userInfoMapper.selectByExample(example);
	
	This result is correct.
	
**Steps to reproduce the behavior, such as: SQL to execute, sharding rule configuration, when exception occur etc.**
	1.Insert 4 million pieces of data

	2.Generate mapper, model, mapper.xml using mybatis-generator

	3.sharding db rule ： ds-$->{0..1}.user_info_$->{0..1}； sharding-table rule ： user_info_$->{user_id % 4 /2}

	4.No exception。

**Example codes for reproduce this issue (such as a github link).**

	Imitate sharding-jdbc-springboot-start to package my own springbootstart

	sharding-jdbc-db : https://gitee.com/vipmos/sharding-jdbc-db.git

	demo springboot project：  https://gitee.com/vipmos/paas-demo.git  use application-sharding2.properties

